1) Kindly check the include path for all the files referred. The paths need to be edited
2) The database has to be create first then you can add your tables to list in the TableList.php
This file helps to restrict the amount of data your database needs to retrieve. Everytime a query is made, you can get the list of 
fields from the array of table list.
You can see examples in the user module.

3) the class Php Crud consists of database queries or function that you can simply pass values to and get the result. There are a 
lot of functions in the class to use including update. 
4) This framework has been specifically used for CRM's.
I will add more instructions later on. Please post any questions if you have. I will reply asap.
